name: Egg Crossbow

name: Fire Beam
description: Fires a sustained beam of energy, dealing damage to all enemies hit.

name: Vacuumulus
description: Emits a powerful shockwave around you, dealing damage to surrounding enemies and rocks.

name: Rain Cloud
description: Summon a cloud that waters any crops it travels over.

name: Chain Lightning
description: Shoots a bolt of lightning at an enemy, damaging them, and then jumping to additional nearby enemies.

name: Fireball
description: Fires a blast of flames, damaging and burning enemies.

name: Earthquake
description: Shake up the earth, instantly tilling land in an area around you.

name: Aegis
description: Increases Armor of all players on the same map and heals them over time.

name: Ethereal Axe
description: Summons a giant magical axe that swings in a large arc in front of you, dealing damage trees.

name: Bubble Net
description: Create an air bubble that floats forward, magically catching any fish that it travels over.

name: Cataclysm
description: Transform into a spinning ball, granting massive movement speed and causing heavy damage to all enemies you collide with during this time.

name: Shadow Rush
description: Tap into your demonic ferocity, increasing your movement speed by 60% for 10 seconds.

name: Miracle
description: Call upon an angelic miracle, restoring 15 Health <color=#39CCFF>plus</color> 15% of your Maximum Health to yourself and nearby players.

name: Elemental Tap
description: Tap into the mana of the earth, restoring 10 Mana <color=#39CCFF>plus</color> 10% of your Maximum Mana to yourself and nearby players.

name: Expert Crafter
description: Your leadership and skills at crafting increase the craft speed of yourself and all players by 20%.

name: Elven Eyes
description: Your elven eyes see much and miss nothing, increasing damage with crossbows by 15%.

name: Primal Nature
description: Your attacks have a chance to restore health. Feel the wild call of battle!

name: Mermaid's Touch
description: Your Mermaid heritage gives you natural fishing skills, increasing the Sweet Spot while landing a fish by 30%.

name: Moo Potion
description: A white potion. Oh wait, no, it's just milk. Magic, potiony milk.

name: Cluck Potion
description: A potion with the creamy color of fresh eggshells. Will it make you lay an egg?

name: Leafy Potion
description: A deep green potion, the same color of the leaves. Probably tastes like leaves, too...

name: Centipede Potion
description: A centipede potion? Is there anything they WON'T make a potion out of these days?

name: Scorched Potion
description: This sizzling crimson potion looks like it puts even the hottest of sauces to shame.

name: Mild Pinchy Potion
description: 'Mild' makes sense, but how exactly can a potion be described as 'pinchy'? Drink it and find out!

name: Spicy Pinchy Potion
description: Prefer a pinch more spice in your transformation potions?

name: Banana Potion
description: This potion sort of looks like a banana smoothie. Maybe it'll taste like one too?

name: Torto Potion
description: The coloration of this potion is difficult to describe. Flat and monotone like a stone, yet shiny and reflective, almost like a turtle shell...

name: Cactus Potion
description: A watery green potion. It smells strongly of cactus flowers.

name: Magma Potion
description: Whew, this potion is almost too hot to handle. It also looks suspiciously like lava...

name: Ice Cube Potion
description: It's a bottle with a giant ice cube in it. The name checks out, at least.

name: Windmill Potion
description: A potion the color of sun faded wood. Even without being touched, the liquid inside the bottle swirls around and around and around...

name: Rock Potion
description: This potion ROCKS! Literally. It turns you into a rock. That's why it's called a rock potion.

name: Bush Potion
description: A box used to be considered the stealthiest of items, but no one expects the bush!

name: Lamp Potion
description: Always wanted to be a street lamp when you grew up? Then do we have the potion for you.

name: Bench Potion
description: Sometimes you just want to sit on a bench and enjoy the sunset... but what if you were the bench?

name: Tree Potion
description: If you didn't know any better, you'd say this potion looked an awful lot like apple juice.

name: Cut Stump Potion
description: Use potion, become stump. The perfect plan.

name: Stool Potion
description: "Better to be a stool than a fool", or at least that's what this potion's tag says.

name: Adventurer's Barrel Potion
description: Ever needed to look sharp? Then this is the potion for you.

name: Garden Barrel Potion
description: Looks like a typical potion, but it smells like a bundle of freshly cut flowers.

name: Dummy Potion
description: A potion the color of hay. Being a dummy has never been easier thanks to this transformation brew.

name: Pointing Potion
description: The perfect potion for those who never want to lose their direction in life.

name: Camping Potion
description: Thankfully this potion smells of burning logs and melting marshmallows, instead of the inside of a tent or something.

name: Delicious Potion
description: The name seems to fit the potion, this looks absolutely delicious to drink.

name: Picnic Potion
description: Best kept away from any ant potions.

name: Chest Potion
description: The real treasure inside this chest is you.

name: Purr-fect Potion
description: A brilliant white potion, almost like milk. It smells faintly of tuna and catnip.

name: Penguin Potion
description: A white and black potion that is perpetually chilly to the touch. It looks like it might taste pretty good.

name: Bunny Potion
description: A white potion with only the faintest hint of pink. It strangely seems as if it would taste of carrots.

name: Rainbow Potion
description: A sparkling potion that constantly shifts between all the colors of the rainbow. Does it taste like rainbows, too?

name: Puppy Potion
description: The potion practically shakes within its bottle as if too excitable to be contained. It smells like... puppy breath.

name: Merchant Potion
description: A rich purple potion. It sounds just like a coin purse if you shake it around.

name: Archmage Potion
description: A fiery red potion. It's sealed with a dab of wax stamped with Sun Haven's crest.

name: Apprentice Potion
description: A mellow orange potion. It smells like the inside of a well-used forge, but it's kind of nice.

name: Doctor Potion
description: A smooth grey potion. It smells like popsicle sticks and cotton balls.

name: Witch Potion
description: A vibrant purple potion. Something about it seems like it'd be great to water plants with.

name: Baker Potion
description: A soft brown potion. Smells like baking bread, with just a hint of stuffed animals.

name: Teacher Potion
description: A shimmering blue potion. If you swirl it around, the blue fades into a black that reminds you oddly of moonlight.

name: Nya Potion
description: A blindingly pink potion. Warning: Drinking this potion will result in the uncontrollable urge to say 'nya'.

name: Enchantress Potion
description: A cool yellow potion. Even for a potion, it seems to glimmer with extra enchantments.

name: Air Mage Potion
description: A bubbly orange potion. If it isn't kept weighted down to the ground, it'll float right away.

name: Knight Potion
description: A deep brown potion. If honor had a smell, this potion just might be it.

name: Spirit Fox Potion
description: A potion of ethereal blue color. The bottle is tightly sealed, yet a wispy smoke still escapes from within it.

name: Silk Potion
description: A potion that seems extra silky smooth. A soft powder floats into and out of the pale liquid inside the bottle.

name: Feather Potion
description: An earthy brown potion that smells a bit like the inside of a nest. Or at least what you'd imagine the inside of a nest must smell like.

name: Stump Potion
description: A woody brown potion, despite being a liquid it somehow seems to have the texture of tree bark.

name: Snake Oil Potion
description: A potion of a deep, menacing hue. Seems a bit viscous, more like an oil than a potion.

name: Peanut Potion
description: A peanut shell-colored potion. For some reason, you feel as if it'd pair nicely with a few acorns or walnuts.

name: Wild Potion
description: A slightly cloudy potion, it swirls and bubbles from within its bottle. It smells of wild and untamed forests.

name: Dragon Potion
description: White and cool in color, but this potion is very much warm in your hands.

name: Elven Lamp Potion
description: A strange orangish-yellowish potion. It emits a good amount of light.

name: Deer Potion
description: A thick brown potion, it gives off a strange aura of forest grace.

name: Slithery Potion
description: A thick black potion with bands of creamy white. It emits a curious hissing sound when shaken.

name: Bad Luck Potion
description: A thin, ink-like potion that gives off a strange and foreboding vibe. The name is just a fun little joke... right?

name: Galaxy Potion
description: A deeply dark potion filled with distant twinkles of stars. Despite being so dark it seems to radiate a bit of light.

name: Fiery Potion
description: Less of a potion and more of a bottle of fire. Drinking this might be a little tricky.

name: Ice Cream Potion
description: Super thick and super pink, if it wasn't labeled as a potion you might think it was just melted ice cream.

name: Shark Potion
description: A grey potion of somewhat gritty consistency. Bound to transform you into a huge vicious shark... or at least a small cute one.

name: Adventurer Potion
description: A wild blue potion. If you had to hazard a guess, you'd say it probably tastes just like meat.

name: Prince Potion
description: A royally red potion. It shines in the light as resplendently as any crown jewel.

name: Queen Potion
description: A hot pink potion. It's just a potion, yet it somehow gives off an aura that makes you feel inferior in its presence.

name: Vampire Potion
description: A somber yellow potion. Even just staring into the swirling liquid makes you feel like sitting down at a piano.

name: Undead Tree Potion
description: A muddy potion that looks as if it has bits of twig and dead leaves floating about in it. It'd take a bit of bravery, or at least boldness, to drink this down.

name: Bookworm Potion
description: A potion supposedly distilled from the plasm of a certain type of spectre. Well, bottoms up?

name: Tablecloth Potion
description: A potion of swirling shadows, you could swear for a brief moment you spotted a pair of white eyes gleaming at you from inside the bottle.

name: Static Potion
description: A potion that... wait... what's that sound? Is that... TV static? From the potion? Weird.

name: Tombstone Potion
description: This potion looks like someone liquified a rock. If spooky forests had a smell, this potion would totally be it.

name: Cheesy Slime Potion
description: An extra thick potion that sloshes slowly around in its bottle. It certainly smells plenty cheesy.

name: Spooky Slime Potion
description: Orange and gooey, this potion seems a lot more like slime than anything else.

name: Sweet Slime Potion
description: A sweet looking pink potion, it seems a bit slime-like but is oddly no less appetizing.

name: Assistant's Potion
description: A leaf-green potion. It looks a tad viscous, like it might be hard to swallow. Hmph!

name: Saltwater Potion
description: A dark and murky potion, mixed with a ladleful of saltwater. Good luck ever forgetting what THIS potion tastes like!

name: Assassin's Potion
description: A nutty aroma with an ever-so-slight hint of rusty dagger. It probably tastes as odd as it smells.

name: Bone Gift
description: A great gift for unusual friends!

name: Love Letter
description: Gift this to an NPC to start dating them.

name: Memory Loss Potion
description: It looks less like a liquid and more like an eerie sort of fog... like a mental haze, obscuring memory and committing it to oblivion.

name: Sapphire
description: A shiny blue sapphire, mined deep from within the earth.

name: Ruby
description: A marvelous red ruby, mined deep from within the earth.

name: Amethyst
description: A gorgeously purple amethyst, mined deep from within the earth.

name: Diamond
description: A person's best friend.

name: Havenite
description: A mysterious and beautiful gem, found only in the earth beneath Sun Haven.

name: Black Diamond
description: A rare black diamond. They're not found very often and are considered a miner's blessing.

name: Copper Ore
description: I can smelt this into a bar.

name: Iron Ore
description: I can smelt this into a bar.

name: Adamant Ore
description: I can smelt this into a bar.

name: Mithril Ore
description: I can smelt this into a bar.

name: Sunite Ore
description: Legendary Sunite, I should try smithing this into a bar.

name: Gold Ore
description: I've struck gold! I can smelt this into a bar.

name: Coal
description: A hard lump of coal, mined from deep within the earth.

name: Glorite Ore
description: A gently pulsating crystal of Glorite ore, it seems to neither reflect nor absorb any light. What could you possibly do with this?

name: Elven Steel Ore
description:
A rare form of iron ore found only in the land of Nel'Vari. Due to a ban on fire crystals, no one in the forest city is sure how to smelt it into bars.

In ancient Nel'Varian the word "steel" roughly translates to "hard as dragon".

name: Fire Crystal
description: The elemental force of fire, hardened into a crystal.

name: Earth Crystal
description: The elemental force of earth, hardened into a crystal.

name: Water Crystal
description: The elemental force of water, hardened into a crystal.

name: Sparkling Dust
description: Shiny flakes of rock and crystal left behind by the passing of wind sprites, Nel'Varians love using it to add sparkle to their creations.

name: Tough Dragon Scale
description: The thick scale of a baby dragon, shed and left behind. It's said that dragon scales can be used in alchemy.

name: Sparkling Dragon Scale
description: The shimmering scale of a baby dragon, shed and left behind. It's said that dragon scales can be used in alchemy.

name: Sharp Dragon Scale
description: The jagged scale of a baby dragon, shed and left behind. It's said that dragon scales can be used in alchemy.

name: Enhanced Copper Bar
description: A copper bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enhanced Iron Bar
description: An iron bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enhanced Adamant Bar
description: An adamant bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enhanced Mithril Bar
description: A mithril bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enhanced Sunite Bar
description: A sunite bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enhanced Glorite Bar
description: A glorite bar, enhanced with Withergate concrete and dark magic.

name: Enchanted Copper Bar
description: A copper bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Enchanted Iron Bar
description: An iron bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Enchanted Adamant Bar
description: An adamant bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Enchanted Mithril Bar
description: A mithril bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Enchanted Sunite Bar
description: A sunite bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Enchanted Glorite Bar
description: A glorite bar, enchanted with Elven magic.

name: Copper Bar
description: A bar of refined copper. Not the strongest metal, but it does the trick.

name: Iron Bar
description: A bar of refined iron. Harder than copper, it will make excellent equipment.

name: Adamant Bar
description: A bar of refined adamant, it's even stronger than iron.

name: Mithril Bar
description: A bar of refined mithril, though beautiful to the eyes its strength and durability are almost unmatched.

name: Sunite Bar
description: A bar of refined sunite, this will produce equipment of legendary quality.

name: Gold Bar
description: A solid gold bar, literally worth its weight in gold!

name: Glorite Bar
description: A bar of Glorite, ready to be turned into something legendary.

name: Elven Steel Bar
description:
Peerless and naturally enchanted steel, it shimmers in the light like a mirror.

"The Nel'Varians lost the technique of forging ore into steel, but why did they learn it in the first place?"

name: Rusty Key
description: An old rusty key, it looks like it opens gates in the mines.

name: Copper Key
description: A copper key crafted especially for the gates in the mines.

name: Iron Key
description: An iron key crafted especially for the gates in the mines.

name: Adamant Key
description: An adamant key crafted especially for the gates in the mines.

name: Mithril Key
description: A mithril key crafted especially for the gates in the mines.

name: Sunite Key
description: A sunite key crafted especially for the gates in the mines, this will lead to the mine's deepest and most dangerous levels.

name: Glorite Key
description: Constructed of Glorite, this key can open the ancient locks of King Minos's Glorite mine.

name: King's Lost Mine Key
description: An ancient key that was held by King Aster, though it became lost after his time. What was Dynus doing with it?

name: King Minos's Emblem
description: An emblem stamped with the seal of King Minos, it grants its bearer access to the Midnight Isle.

name: Wind Orb
description: "I must admit, Nivara was right... I had the potential to master this magic all along." - Vaan

name: Stone
description: A lump of ordinary rock, I bet it could be crafted into some sort of stonework.

name: Log
description: A hunk of hewn tree, just waiting to be turned into planks.

name: Wood Plank
description: I can craft lots of things with this!

name: Silk
description: A soft sheet of silk, great for crafting.

name: Fabric
description: Not as soft as silk, but very durable.

name: Hardwood
description: A log of hewn Hardwood, far more durable than ordinary wood. It's just waiting to be turned into planks.

name: Hardwood Plank
description: A plank of Hardwood, true to its name these planks are heavy! Used in advanced crafting recipes.

name: Hardwood Beam
description: A solid beam of Hardwood, usable in crafting. Beam me up!

name: Wood Beam
description: A solid beam of wood, usable in crafting. Beam me up!

name: Dead Log
description: The zombified log of a haunted tree, ready to be turned into planks.

name: Dead Hardwood
description: The zombified log of a haunted hardwood tree, ready to be turned into planks.

name: Dead Plank
description: Night of the living plank? Nah, just a deadwood plank. Used in Withergate crafting.

name: Dead Hardwood Plank
description: Night of the living plank? Nah, just a heavy deadwood plank. Used in Withergate crafting.

name: Dead Stone
description: A dark rock from the haunted forests of Withergate. You're not sure why, but something about it feels... wrong.

name: Dead Heavystone
description: An extra hard dark rock from the haunted forests of Withergate. You're not sure why, but something about it feels... wrong.

name: Elven Log
description: A log of Elven wood, shimmering with mana and ready to be turned into planks.

name: Elven Hardwood
description: A log of Elven hardwood, shimmering with mana and ready to be turned into planks.

name: Elven Plank
description: Enchanted wood, now in convenient plank form. Used in Nel'Varian crafting.

name: Elven Hardwood Plank
description: Enchanted Hardwood, now in convenient plank form. Used in advanced Nel'Varian crafting.

name: Elven Stone
description: A rock mined from the Nel'Vari mines. Like everything else in Nel'Vari, it feels slightly magical.

name: Elven Heavystone
description: An extra hard rock mined from the Nel'Vari mines. Like everything else in Nel'Vari, it feels slightly magical.

name: Refined Plastic
description: Perhaps Demonkind's most pivotal invention, 'soft metal' - easy to shape, and lasts a very, very long time.

name: Refined Glass
description: Do you have any idea how much glass this city is going to need? - Xyla

name: Refined Metal
description: A bunch of scrap metals melted down and turned into an alloy. It's messy, but it works.

name: Refined Concrete
description: A key Demon invention, who needs to chisle bricks from mountains when you can simply make your own?

name: Tin Foil
description: Makes good hats.

name: Fire Rune
description: A magical sealing rune, containing the element of fire.

name: Crystal Cluster
description: A small cluster of crystals, they look freshly formed and brimming with mana.

name: Driftwood
description: Slightly waterlogged from its time adrift, it will still make some fine planks.

name: Sand Dollar
description: I wonder if this is what fish use as money?

name: Starfish
description: Neither a fish nor a star, but still pretty neat looking.

name: Clam
description: This would go great in a nice chowder.

name: Ocean Treasure Chest
description: A sunken chest of long lost booty!

name: Fallen Log
description: Nature did the chopping for you. How convenient.

name: Feather
description: The fledgling feathers of baby griffons are famously known for their softness.

name: Peanuts
description: Coveted by squirrels, these shelled nuts are often left behind as gifts to those who have befriended the furry critters.

name: Dragon Scale
description: Though comparatively tiny compared to a scale from a fully grown dragon, it's still harder than mithril.

name: Cat Nip
description: Cats usually keep this potent herb safely guarded, though they are known to drop some when excited.

name: Wool
description: A bundle of pure wool, this animal product will sell for a fair price.

name: Golden Wool
description: A bundle of pure golden wool, this golden animal product will sell for a high price.

name: Golden Log
description: Who needs gold leaf when you've got gold log? This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Golden Feather
description: Solid gold, yet no heavier than a normal feather. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Golden Silk
description: Luxurious silk woven of pure gold. This golden product will sell for a high price.

name: Sandstone Ore
description: A dusty chunk of sandstone, you wouldn't want to drop this on your toes.

name: Sandstone Fish
description: Though an average size fish, its solid sandstone scales make it quite heavy.

name: Heavystone
description: A lump of extra hard rock, useful in advanced stonework.

name: Unrefined Plastic
description: Unrefined building materials, they could be used in crafting.

name: Unrefined Glass
description: Unrefined building materials, they could be used in crafting.

name: Unrefined Metal
description: Unrefined building materials, they could be used in crafting.

name: Unrefined Concrete
description: Unrefined building materials, they could be used in crafting.

name: Jazz Record
description: A smooth jazz tune to kick back and relax to.

name: Regal Record
description: Playing this record will make your humble farmhouse feel like a royal castle.

name: Bossa Record
description: You'll have to learn to mambo if you're going to play this record!

name: Waltz Record
description: Care for a dance?

name: Celtic Record
description: A selection of rousing instruments that is certain to get your blood pumping.

name: Lo-Fi Record
description: Chill beats to grow crops to.

name: Folk Record
description: A folksy tune, perfect for chopping some wood to.

name: Lullaby Record
description: A soothing melody, you're likely to fall right asleep listening to this.

name: Music Box Record
description: A music box song recorded onto a record... unconventional, but it sounds great!

name: Sentimental Record
description: A sentimental arrangement with the power to move people and castles alike.

name: Rain Record

description: Definitely not a monster of the ferocious type, this cute plushie looks like it'd much rather make friends than scare people.

name: Double Headed Cat Plushie
description: Two heads just means this plushie will have to get twice the ear scratchies.

name: Bee Plushie
description: A soft bumble bee plushie, just as cute as the real thing and significantly less likely to sting when you hug it.

name: Ghost Plushie
description: This plushie holds its ghostly little arms out as if to frighten you, though it really it just looks like it's asking for a hug.

name: Candy Plushie
description: Candy is dandy and plushies are... well, nothing cute rhymes with 'plushie', but the point is that this candy plushie is a real treat.

name: Spider Plushie
description: Eight legs of pure plushie adorableness, how can even the most serious spider-hater say no to this cute little guy?

name: Mystic Orb
description: Warning: Orb may cause spontanious bouts of pondering.

name: Squid Plushie
description: Squid are at home in the dark depths of the deep ocean. This little plushie squid, on the other hand, would be most at home on your couch.

name: Bat Tea Set
description: The kettle and cups are made of black porcelain clay, collected from the marshlands around Withergate. The bat is just along for the ride.

name: Spiderweb Painting
description: A web of spider silk, depicted as a painting. Very goth, very spider.

name: Cauldron
description: The contents of this bubbling cauldron is unknown, but you can bet every last one of your tickets that it is most assuredly of the wicked variety.

name: Bat Window
description: Found yourself stuck choosing between getting a window or getting bats? Why not get BOTH? You deserve it.

name: Bat Monster Statue
description: A fiendishly chiseled statue of dark stone, the gemstone eyes almost seem to follow your every movement.

name: Moon Mirror
description: It isn't the easiest mirror to use, but why should functionality come before style?

name: Moon Banner
description: An ornate tapestry that beautifully depicts a starry night sky, it wouldn't look out of place even hanging in Withergate's castle.

name: Pumpkin Plushie
description: If this plushie ever got a hole in it, what would you patch it with? A PUMPKIN patch.

name: Bat Plushie
description: Small and fuzzy, this plushie could almost be mistaken for the real thing.

name: Candy Corn Plushie
description: This plushie might not be yummy like the real candy, but with his happy face and super soft stuffing, it's got a sweetness of its very own.

name: Shooting Star Plushie
description: Throw this plushie over your head and make a wish. It probably won't work, but it'll be cute.

name: Snaccoon Plushie
description: Fed plenty of wool stuffing, this chubby plushie is ready for a nice long nap at your place.

name: Sprinkles Plushie
description: A plushie modeled after the famous pet, now you can have TWICE the Sprinkles fun.

name: Charon Plushie
description: Withergate's trusty and ever-working boat-hound, now collectable in plushie form.

name: Slobert Plushie
description: Oh, a plushie of Slobert. And look, it's made out of slime. How wonderful.

name: Chubby Dynus Plushie
description: Can plushies be menacing? Dynus's plushie is here to say that yes, plushies CAN be menacing.

name: Withergate Fence
description: Metal fencing that is as durable as it is imposing. Any would-be invaders will think twice before stepping foot onto your farm.

name: Small Withergate Lamp
description: Demons in Withergate have perfected the art of glassblowing, allowing them to mass produce funky table lamps such as this.

name: Medium Withergate Lamp
description: A heavy bulb of glass blown from marsh sand. A sturdy iron pole keeps it hanging for a unique look.

name: Bent Withergate Lamp
description: The iron pole of this hanging lamp was accidentally bent during production, which just adds another dimension of style.

name: Large Withergate Lamp
description: Designed by Xyla herself as an original pitch for Withergate city streetlights, these didn't quite make the cut. The design has been repurposed into a line of floor lamps, like this one, however.

name: Squid Monster Statue
description: An ancient statue recovered from the Withergate swamps, it depicts a member of a primordial race that lived in the area long before the monsters came.

name: Jack'O'Rug
description: The grinning visage of a jack'o'lantern has been eternally captured in the fabric of this snazzy rug.

name: Nightsky Rug
description: Maybe you can't walk through the sky, but you can at least walk ON it with this plush purple rug.

name: Monster Fireplace
description: A great place to warm your feet... or your claws, or your tentacles, or your slime or... whatever else you like to warm.

name: Alien Plushie
description: Aliens may be out of this world, but this squishy plushie sure isn't. Pick him up today and take him to your leader.

name: Turtle Plushie
description: A squishy plushie turtle buddy, he could definitely get anyone to come out of their shell.

name: Fidget Spinner
description: Made of counterbalanced weights that keep spinning when given a flick. The citizens of Withergate are oddly divided on whether this toy is awesome or obnoxious.

name: Finger Traps
description: Brought to Withergate from a far away land, you'll never get them off your fingers by pulling them apart. The trick is to push your fingers together.

name: Puzzle Cube
description: A puzzle of colored tiles, you could spend hours trying to figure out the correct solution.

name: Piggy Bank
description: A clay piggy with a slot in his back for tickets, what a quaint little idea.

name: Fuzzy Dice
description: Feeling lucky? These fuzzy novelty dice quickly became a popular decoration in Withergate homes, though no one is quite sure why.

name: Tailor Store Model
description: A model replica created by Xyla of the Withergate tailor shop. Does it come with a little model Arianella, too?

name: Pool Table
description: A game of Demon invention, players use sticks to knock balls into holes. The clack of the marble balls striking one another is almost iconic in itself.

name: Plain Pumpkin
description: Fresh from the patch and ready for any and all forms of pumpkin-related shenanigans.

name: Witch Pumpkin
description: Which pumpkin is the witch pumpkin? Oh, it's the one with the witch's hat! Obviously.

name: Monstrous Pumpkin
description: Someone went the extra mile to make this grinning jack-o-lantern look especially fiendish!

name: Pumpkin Carriage
description: Yes, this is a carriage made out of a giant hollowed out pumpkin. To an outsider it might seem strange, but to Withergate's nobility this is a first class ride.

name: Year of the Rabbit Plush
description: A cute plushie honoring the zodiac year of the rabbit.

name: Year of the Horse Plush
description: A cute plushie honoring the zodiac year of the horse.

name: Year of the Ram Plush
description: A cute plushie honoring the zodiac year of the ram.

name: Year of the Tiger Plush
description: A cute plushie honoring the zodiac year of the tiger.

description: A cute plushie honoring the zodiac year of the rat.

description: A cute plushie honoring the zodiac year of the rooster.

description: A cute plushie honoring the zodiac year of the pig.

name: Year of the Snake Plush
description: A cute plushie honoring the zodiac year of the snake.

name: Festive Oranges
description: Special oranges picked for the lantern festival.

name: Spicy Shrimp Ramen
description: Tiny shrimp fried in extra hot pepper sauce, ramen doesn't taste meaner than this.

name: Pork Ramen
description: Rice noodles are noodles made with rice, so it's sort of like two foods in one. Sort of.

name: Egg Ramen
description: Delicate egg noodles floating in a savory broth, topped with hard boiled eggs. Eggsactly what you need for the perfect bowl of ramen.

name: Moon Cake
description: A festive and delicious cake that is best shared with friends and family to truly celebrate the lantern festival.

name: Year of the Dragon Plush
description: A cute plushie honoring the zodiac year of the dragon.

name: Lantern Festival Selling Portal
description: A mystical portal linked directly to merchants ready to buy your lantern festival goodies.

name: Silly Chicken Lantern
description: Sheets of paper elegantly arranged to resemble a colorful silly chicken, commemorating a successful lantern festival.

name: Chicken Lantern
description: Sheets of paper elegantly arranged to resemble a colorful chicken, commemorating a successful lantern festival.

name: Rooster Lantern
description: Sheets of paper elegantly arranged to resemble a colorful rooster, commemorating a successful lantern festival.

name: Chick Lantern
description: Sheets of paper elegantly arranged to resemble a colorful chick, commemorating a successful lantern festival.

name: Paper Lantern Strand
description: Soft candles burn within the paper lanterns, reminding those who look at them to let go of their past selves and embrace new ones.

name: Box Paper Lantern
description: Made of rice paper dyed in festive colors, take this home and then every night can be your own mini-lantern festival!

name: Hourglass Paper Lantern
description: Made of rice paper dyed in festive colors, take this home and then every night can be your own mini-lantern festival!

name: Tapered Paper Lantern
description: Made of rice paper dyed in festive colors, take this home and then every night can be your own mini-lantern festival!

name: Chow Mein
description: "Chow mein" translates to "Fried noodles", which is a very fitting named, considering this dish is made primarily of fried noodles!

name: Apple Cider
description: Ripe apples, pressed into a pulpy juice and spiced to cidery perfection.

name: Strawberry Milk
description: Milk... from a strawberry? Nah, just strawberry flavored cow milk!

name: Blueberry Muffin
description: A perfectly baked muffin dotted with juicy little blueberries.

name: Fruit Punch
description: A tropical drink that originated in the sunny Southern Islands, it's become a staple drink at parties and celebrations.

name: Raspberry Crepes
description: A crepe is like a fancy little pancake, filled with sweet raspberries it makes an extra yummy treat.

name: Fruit Tart
description: Aptly named, this pastry has a sharp tart kick in contrast to the sweet fruit and sugary crust.

name: Linguine with Clams
description: Thick sauce and noodles served with steamed clams, a great choice for a filling seafood meal.

name: Peaches and Cream
description: Sliced peaches served in a creamed milk sauce. This is sometimes used as the filling for a pie but it's just as good on its own.

name: Tikka Masala
description: Seared vegetables in a searingly spicy sauce, it's quite delicious if you can make it past the heat.

name: California Roll
description: A type of sushi roll native to a far, far away and mythical land that is only spoken about in legends.

name: Fish Taco
description: A little different from what most people think of when it comes to "tacos", but still very delicious.

name: Creamy Mushroom Soup
description: In the past this simple soup was made due to a lack for any better ingredients. Today, however, it's an old fashioned comfort food classic.

name: Waffles
description: Light and airy on the inside, but golden and crunchy on the outside. All that's missing is a slab of butter and a bucket of syrup.

name: Nachos
description: If they're nacho chips, then who's are they? They're mine!

name: Lobster Roll
description: Seasoned lobster meat, served in a hotdog bun of all things. A bit strange, but it totally works.

name: Pad Thai
description: Stir-fried noodles and nuts, this is served as a popular street food in cities all over the four regions.

name: Lasagna
description: A classic dish from the Eastern Region, layers of sauce and noodles that make for a hearty dinner meal.

name: Potato Salad
description: A gooey mixture of potatoes and egg, it's not like any salad you've ever heard of before but it's pretty tasty.

name: Ice Cream
description: It's just milk and honey churned in ice, but it's irresistably delicious.

name: Yogurt Parfait
description: Yogurt and strawberries, layered together and topped with honeyed oats. Unbeatable when it comes to being quick, simple and delicious.

name: Omelet
description: A basic egg dish, great for breakfast. Or lunch. Or dinner. Or whenever!

name: Fish and Chips
description: Deep fried fish served with a side of chips, can you believe some people actually call them "fries"?!

name: Lobster Bisque
description: Soft chunks of delicate lobster meat, swimming in a thick and creamy soup.

name: Grilled Cheese
description: Many a beginner chef's first dish, its simplicity does not subtract from its yummyness.

name: Onion Rings
description: Onion slices, breaded and fried in oil. Vegetables don't taste better than this.

name: Sweet and Spicy Shrimp
description: Sweetness and spiciness battle each other for dominance in this shrimp dish. The winner of their duel? Your tastebuds.

name: Seafood Gumbo
description: A thin stew of assorted crustaceans, its spice and heat perfectly accent the tender seafood.

name: Poke Bowl
description: Seasoned fish served over rice, simple fare often enjoyed by sailors while out at sea.

name: Apple Sauce
description: A soft 'sauce' of mashed apples, easy to make and even easier to eat.

name: Veggie Kebab
description: Skewered veggies roasted over an open flame, the crisp taste of the fire adds a remarkably complex taste to the veggies.

name: Strawberry Shortcake
description: Some people enjoy letting the juice of the strawberry soak into the shortcake, while others try to eat it before that can happen.

name: Mochi Covered Strawberry
description: A strawberry, covered in a thin layer of flavored mochi. A lightweight but lovely dessert.

name: Acai Bowl
description: Sweet yogurt topped with an assortment of berries, a common breakfast food for many across the land.

name: Citrus Salad
description: Fragrant and slightly tangy, it's very invigorating for only being a 'mere' salad.

name: Fruit Snacks
description: Squishly little fruit snacks, an even more fun way to eat your fruits.

name: Tuna Nigiri
description: Raw fish can taste good? Who would have thought.

name: Tortilla Chips
description: A corn tortilla, cut up and turned into delicious crunchy chips thanks to the magic of deep frying.

name: Salsa
description: A loose sauce of tomato and spices, its zesty zing certainly dresses up all sorts of dishes.

name: Mushroom Risotto
description: Labor intensive to prepare, but the savory mushroom mixed with the twice-cooked rice is an excellent reward for the effort.

name: Mochi
description: Sweetened rice paste, shaped into a spongey cake and steamed before baking.

name: Mushroom Stroganoff
description: Roast mushrooms, drenched in a thick and savory broth. A peasant meal, but still fit for a king.

name: Veggie Wrap
description: Diced veggies wrapped in a corn tortilla, the soft wrap contrasts well against the crunchy vegetables inside.

name: Trail Mix
description: A mix of energy-boosting food to keep one fueled over long adventures.

name: Churros
description: Dough sticks, fried in oil and breaded with sugar. Simple, yet very delicious.

name: Tortilla
description: A corn tortilla made of corn flour dough and baked over an open fire, it's like bread only... super flat.

name: Corn Flour
description: Made of finely milled corn. It's heavier than wheat flour and slightly sweeter, too.

name: Hydrangea Cupcake
description: A cupcake topped with an intricately piped frosting design, world famous pastry chef Ramiro is credited for inventing this style of frosting.

name: Chicken Bastilla
description: Shredded chicken wrapped in layers of paper-thin dough. This delicious pastry was the signature dish of Raine, a world-famous chef and culinary visionary.

name: Dumplings
description: What's a lantern festival without dumplings? Let's hope we never have to find out.

name: Rice Ball Soup
description: The rice balls aren't actually made out of rice, but a dough made from rice flour. "Rice flour ball soup" just doesn't sound as nice, though.

name: Mining Essence
description: Ancient Nel'Varian mana, distilled into a consumable potion. This one contains the essence of earthen caverns and stone.

name: Fisherman's Essence
description: Ancient Nel'Varian mana, distilled into a consumable potion. This one contains the essence of rivers and streams.

name: Woodcutter's Essence
description: Ancient Nel'Varian mana, distilled into a consumable potion. This one contains the essence of deep forests and the trees.

name: Fortitude Essence
description: Distilled essence of ancient Nel'Varian mana, it bestows fortitude when tapped.

name: Mind Essence
description: Distilled essence of ancient Nel'Varian mana, it bestows mental stamina when tapped.

name: Arcane Essence
description: Distilled essence of ancient Nel'Varian mana, it bestows arcanic might when tapped.

name: Defense Essence
description: Distilled essence of ancient Nel'Varian mana, it bestows increased defenses when tapped.

name: Strength Essence
description: Distilled essence of ancient Nel'Varian mana, it bestows great strength when tapped.

name: Limited Edition Dynus Plushie
description: Only a handful of these limited edition plushies were ever created. Owing to their rarity, and Dynus's celebrity status, this is one of the hottest pieces of merchandise one could get their hands (or claws) on.

name: Rock Candy Gem
description:
This is taking the idea of "rock candy" a bit too literally...

This candy gem can be used as a potion ingredient at the alchemy table.

name: Hard Butterscotch Gem
description:
This gemstone looks just like a yummy butterscotch candy. Hopefully it tastes like it, too.

This candy gem can be used as a potion ingredient at the alchemy table.

name: Jawbreaker Gem
description:
Think normal jawbreakers are hard? Try eating one made out of solid gemstone!

This candy gem can be used as a potion ingredient at the alchemy table.

name: Small Blue Glorite Crystal
description:
Crystalized mana and power, in the form of blue glorite. It can be drained to increase your maximum mana. Elios warned you of the negative effects of consuming glorite's power... but he isn't here right now, is he?

Blue glorite is said to fuel Dynus's inexhaustible mana reserves.

description:
A powerful potion brewed from the candy gems found in the monsterfolk lands.

"You want my favor... yet you offer me mere candy? Monsterfolk... are so foolish." - Dynus

name: Incredible Attack Potion
description:
A powerful potion brewed from the candy gems found in the monsterfolk lands.

"Such power this 'candy' possesses... perhaps the monsterfolk have something to offer me after all." - Dynus

name: Incredible Defense Potion
description:
A powerful potion brewed from the candy gems found in the monsterfolk lands.

"The monsterfolk shall have a home in Withergate... and I shall have their tribute." - Dynus

name: Withergate Mining Potion
description: Made of melted candy and lots of sugar, it's the perfect energy boost for breaking stuff faster as you work in the Withergate mines.

name: Withergate Snaccoon Plush
description: Living in the dangerous forests of Withergate must be very hard... unless you're an eight hundred pound snaccoon who eats anything it wants!

name: Nel'Vari Snaccoon Plush
description: The snaccoons of Nel'Vari really love their fruits and berries, the Elven forests are rich with them, after all.

name: Explorer Snaccoon Plush
description: A snaccoon plush that is ready to explore the wide world with you!

name: Farmer Snaccoon Plush
description: A snaccoon plush that can't wait to grow all sorts of delicious crops with you!

name: Bunny Snaccoon Plush
description: A snaccoon plush that thinks it's a bunny. How cute!

name: Beach Snaccoon Plush
description: A snaccoon plush that is ready to hit the beach and soak up some summer rays!

name: Miner Snaccoon Plush
description: A snaccoon plush that is miner is style, but not minor in cuteness!

name: Angler Snaccoon Plush
description: This snacoon plush couldn't be bothered to wait for someone to feed him fish, so he grabbed a rod and got to work!

name: Ghost Snaccoon Plush
description: A spooky snaccoon ghost plush! Don't worry, though, it's just a costume.

name: Vampire Snaccoon Plush
description: A snaccoon plush that vants to eat your food, blah blah.

name: Cowboy Snaccoon Plush
description: A snaccoon plush that is at home under a starry sky on the open range. Your bedroom would be fine, too.

name: Pajama Snaccoon Plush
description: Snaccoons do two things: eat and sleep. This snaccoon is pajama'd up and ready for a nap!

name: Camper Snaccoon Plush
description: Snaccoons love to camp. Well, they love to walk to places and fall asleep, which is sort of like camping.

name: Scarf Snaccoon Plush
description: A little snaccoon plush that's all bundled up and ready for winter!

description: It looks just like an ice cream you dropped on the beach! It also tastes like one, too.

description: Can't choose between having cheesecake or ice cream? Now you don't have to!

description: A tooth-breaking dessert straight from the stone age.

description: The spicy cinnamon mixed with the sweet ice cream produces a fairly complex flavor profile. Yummy!
